04/07/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- The head of the Serbian Security Information Agency, Rade Bulatovic, said on Friday (1 July) that the security situation in the country is stable and that he expects no deterioration.
Bulatovic was presenting a confidential report about the agency's work to parliament's defence and security committee.
In other news, Serbian Deputy Prime Minister Miroljub Labus reaffirmed on Saturday that Serbia-Montenegro would likely begin talks on a Stabilisation and Association Agreement with the EU on 5 October.
He added that in parallel to the EU integration process, the process of the federal union's accession to the WTO is under way.
(Tanjug, RTS - 02/07/05;
Beta - 01/07/05)
